=========================================================
new vs operator new (INTERVIEW NOTES) ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
=========================================================

new
----
• new is a C++ operator.
• Allocates memory by calling operator new().
• Calls the constructor.
• Returns a typed pointer.
• Throws std::bad_alloc on allocation failure.

Example:
int* p = new int(10);

---------------------------------------------------------

operator new()
--------------
• operator new() is a function.
• Only allocates raw memory.
• Does NOT call the constructor.
• Returns void*.
• Can be overloaded for custom memory allocation.

Example:
void* p = operator new(sizeof(int));

---------------------------------------------------------

What happens internally?

int* p = new int(10);

Internally:

1. operator new(sizeof(int));   // Allocate memory
2. Constructor initializes object (stores 10)
3. Return int*

---------------------------------------------------------

Difference

new
• C++ operator
• Allocates memory + calls constructor
• Returns typed pointer
• Used for object creation

operator new()
• Function
• Allocates raw memory only
• Does NOT call constructor
• Returns void*
• Used for custom memory management

---------------------------------------------------------

Interview Questions

Q. Is new a function?
Ans: No. It is an operator.

Q. Does operator new() call the constructor?
Ans: No.

Q. Who calls operator new()?
Ans: The new operator.

Q. Can operator new() be overloaded?
Ans: Yes.

---------------------------------------------------------

Interview One-liner

The new operator allocates memory using operator new(), constructs the object by calling 
its constructor, and returns a typed pointer. The operator new() function only allocates raw memory and does not construct the object.

=========================================================

---------------------------------------------------------

new performs FOUR operations

1. Calls operator new() to allocate memory.
2. Allocates raw memory.
3. Calls constructor.
4. Returns typed pointer.

Example:

Test* ptr = new Test();

Internally (conceptually):

void* mem = operator new(sizeof(Test));

Test* ptr = new(mem) Test;

---------------------------------------------------------

operator new()

Only allocates raw memory.

It DOES NOT call constructor.

