3. Virtual Destructor with delete ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐*******VVVVVVVVIMP
=========================================================

Whenever a base pointer points to a derived object,
the base class should have a virtual destructor.

Example

class Base
{
public:

    virtual ~Base()
    {
        cout<<"Base Destructor"<<endl;
    }
};

class Derived : public Base
{
public:

    ~Derived()
    {
        cout<<"Derived Destructor"<<endl;
    }
};

int main()
{
    Base* ptr = new Derived;

    delete ptr;
}

Output

Derived Destructor

Base Destructor

---------------------------------------------------------

Without virtual destructor

Deleting through Base*

↓

Undefined Behavior

Derived destructor may not execute.

Resources owned by Derived may leak.

